@node _intro "What is PairsNG ?"
@font helvetica.font 11

@{b} Introduction / Playing PairsNG@{ub}

  PairsNG is a board game of Shanghai style.

  You may choose between three different skill modes:

  Beginner:@{Tab}12 * 8 stones@{Tab}240 seconds time
  Normal:@{Tab}18 * 12 stones@{Tab}480 seconds time
  Profi:@{Tab}24 * 16 stones@{Tab}860 seconds time
  
  The stones are mixed and build up randomly to the board. 

  You have to break up all stones from the board in the given time. 

  Choose a stone and click on it - the stone will be stored, now click on another
  one of the same kind; the program is attempting to draw a line now.

  The clicked stones will only be breaked up, if there is a direct line between the two
  stones. Is the line blocked from another stone, this does not work. The line between
  the stones may snap off twice in 90 degrees.

  If you managed to draw a line, it will be displayed for a short moment. You get 10 points
  for each breakupped pair.

  Are all stones are breaked up - you get a time bonus for the rest time. The next level
  starts with a new board, but @{b}time will be reduced 30 seconds for each level !@{ub}
  
  Bonus points for each pair: 5 Points per second

  If alle stones are broke up, the game is over.

  
  @{b}Item fields:@{ub}
  The stones are black-yellow lined. If such a pair is choosen, you will get one of twelve
  different items. This items can be positive or negative - time, points or stones.

  You don't need to build up item fields - you are free in your decision ;-)

